16	20057a55-6b77-4c33-836d-f01c76b283a4	gmail	19a2b422661d4630	email	Discover more with your Upstash free account	*****************\r\nUpstash Use Cases\r\n*****************\r\n\r\nWe hope you've enjoyed using the Upstash free version over the past week. We'd like to share some of the popular use cases that Upstash is utilized to give you insights into how others are maximizing the benefits of our products.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n*******************************************************************************\r\nBuild an authenticated API ( https://upstash.com/blog/authenticated-api-redis )\r\n*******************************************************************************\r\n\r\nHere you can check an example ( https://upstash.com/blog/authenticated-api-redis ) of authenticated Rest API service that leverages Next.js API Routes and Upstash Database, that is used as a storage and cache system for user data, for user authentication, and for JWT handling\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n*****************************************************************************************************\r\nAdding page view analytics to your blogs ( https://upstash.com/blog/nextjs13-approuter-view-counter )\r\n*****************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nHere article ( https://upstash.com/blog/nextjs13-approuter-view-counter ) explains how to create a view counter on your blog using Upstash Database that tracks all visits and increments counter for each unique visitor\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n*********************************************************\r\nUpstash OpenAI ( https://upstash.com/blog/redis-openapi )\r\n*********************************************************\r\n\r\nThis article ( https://upstash.com/blog/redis-openapi ) summarizes the most common use cases that we see developers are using Upstash with OpenAI and other AI APIs such as Google Cloud AI, IBM Watson, Hugging Face.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThese are some of the examples you can test and iterate on multiple MVPs without worrying about an enormous bill for an app that might not even have users yet. Enjoy and keep innovating and as you scale your apps, check out our Pay as you Go plan ( https://upstash.com/pricing ) that gives you full control and transparency on your bills.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest,\r\nUpstash Support Team\r\n\r\n Twitter ( https://twitter.com/upstash )LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/upstash/ )Discord ( https://upstash.com/discord )\r\nAbout ( https://upstash.com/about )     Terms ( https://upstash.com/trust/terms.pdf )     Contact ( https://upstash.com/docs/common/help/support )\r\n\r\nThe email was sent to viktorstrindin93@gmail.com.\r\n\r\nTo no longer receive these emails, unsubscribe ( https://track.customer.io/unsubscribe/dgSrzggBAN-5JN65JAGaK0IgvuerCOJbnNDQ-ww= ) here.\r\n\r\n©2025 Upstash, Inc\r\nupstash.com	{"to": "viktorstrindin93@gmail.com", "date": "Tue, 28 Oct 2025 14:39:05 +0000", "from": "Upstash <support@upstash.com>", "snippet": "Upstash Use Cases We hope you&#39;ve enjoyed using the Upstash free version over the past week. We&#39;d like to share some of the popular use cases that Upstash is utilized to give you insights into", "analysis": {"summary": "Upstash is following up after a week of free account usage to showcase popular use cases for their product. The email highlights three main examples: building authenticated APIs, adding page view analytics, and integrating with OpenAI and other AI services. This is a typical onboarding/engagement email designed to encourage continued product usage.", "category": "newsletter", "priority": "low", "sentiment": "positive", "actionItems": ["Review the three use case examples if interested in implementing similar features", "Consider upgrading from free tier if scaling applications"]}, "labelIds": ["CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS", "UNREAD", "INBOX"], "threadId": "19a2b422661d4630"}	\N	0.49999999999999994	2025-10-28 14:39:05	2025-10-29 06:34:41.36
