43	20057a55-6b77-4c33-836d-f01c76b283a4	gmail	19a27db10fc63e5a	email	Apple’s M5 Chip is the Comeback No One Saw Coming	The Atlas\r\n\r\nAv Generative AI\r\n\r\n\r\nAv Generative AI\r\n\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    Läs den här artikeln på LinkedIn för att delta i konversationen\r\nLäs på LinkedIn\r\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/apples-m5-chip-comeback-one-saw-coming-genai-works-mlt7f?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BKRdd92ZfQEqDM42cdEy4AQ%3D%3D&midToken=AQFnXqLnGXqsGA&midSig=1i6HJ7gQ3n_XY1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-h01i2f~mh9qaam1~s1-null-null&eid=h01i2f-mh9qaam1-s1&otpToken=MTMwNTFjZTcxYjI3Y2NjNGIyMmQwZmViNDExOGU2YjI4ZmNiZDI0NDllYWU4OTZjN2JjZjA0NmQ0YTVkNTlmYWY1ZGNkNmU5NTZlNWU2ODIwZThiZDZiZGJkNGY1MThhYTI4Yzk3MmY3OGFmOTAzNmZhMTg2MWQ0LDEsMQ%3D%3D\r\n  \r\nApple is finally done playing defense, unleashing a new chip that makes on-device AI unbelievably fast. Meanwhile, Microsoft is bringing back a fan-favorite 'ghost' from the past to guide its future, and two key enterprise players, Anthropic and Mistral, are building the actual infrastructure that the entire business world will run on. If you thought AI innovation was slowing down, think again. This Week's AI Headlines: Apple's M5: The Chip With a Built-In Brain Microsoft: Clippy Returns as Copilot's Hidden Ghost Open-Source Data: Apple's New Gift to AI Research Anthropic: Claude Code Turns Browser into Dev Lab Mistral AI: Building the Enterprise DevOps Layer Special highlight from our network From answers to agents: the future of enterprise knowledge discovery Imagine AI that’s grounded in your content, built to scale relevance, optimize accuracy, and prove ROI.  Get a first look at foundational AI built for every point-of-experience. Join Lynsey Price, Scott Ferguson, and Oscar Péré (Coveo) for a live demo of what's new in Coveo’s AI Relevance Platform: Agentforce actions in action Expanding API suite for full customization Tools for both managed and custom builds Optimized for AWS Bedrock, SAP Joule, and more Live on October 29, 2025 at 11:00 a.m. ET Register to attend Apple’s M5 is the Most Powerful AI Chip in Its History. But How Far Can It Really Go? A neural accelerator in every GPU core Apple has finally built a chip that takes AI seriously. The new M5 adds a neural accelerator to every GPU core, giving the processor a kind of built-in brain. It’s four times faster at AI tasks than the M4, has 30% more memory bandwidth, and includes a new GPU made to handle real-time reasoning and graphics at once. ● Neural GPU cores. Each core can now handle image generation, vision models, and smaller AI systems directly through Apple’s own Metal software. ● Faster memory. The M5 moves data at 153 GB/s, fast enough to run local AI tools without depending on the cloud. ● Smarter CPU. Ten cores designed for mixed workloads bring a 15% lift in performance. ● AI-ready graphics. The GPU renders light and reflections 45% faster, making it easier to blend design, gaming, and generative work. For a long time, Apple stayed behindt while the rest of the tech world raced into AI. NVIDIA powered the boom, Microsoft and Google built assistants, and OpenAI became a household name. Apple stayed in the background, focused on privacy and hardware. The M5 changes that story. It brings AI to the heart of Apple’s devices, right where people use them every day. This chip is giving Macs and iPads the ability to think for themselves, to create, edit, and respond without sending your data anywhere else. After years on the sidelines, Apple is finally building the kind of intelligence that lives in your hands, not in someone else’s server room. Apple Open-Sources Its Best AI Training Data Yet Pico-Banana-400K could redefine how visual models learn to edit the real world. Apple has released Pico-Banana-400K, a 400,000-image dataset for text-guided image editing. It may be one of the most advanced AI resources ever shared publicly. The collection is built to teach models how to modify real photographs with precision and context. ● Real-world foundation. Most datasets rely on computer-generated imagery. Pico-Banana draws from real photos in the OpenImages collection, processed by Apple’s internal system Nano-Banana. ● Dual AI pipeline. One model performed the edits. Another, Google’s Gemini 2.5 Pro, acted as the reviewer and selected only the most accurate and lifelike results. ● Learning judgment. The dataset includes 56,000 examples showing both successful and failed edits, giving models a reference for what works. It also contains 72,000 multi-edit sequences that show how complex transformations build up step by step. ● Open access. The full dataset is publicly available for researchers who want to study AI-driven photo editing. Pico-Banana-400K signals a turning point. Machines are beginning to create and verify their own training data. Apple just gave the world a working model for how self-taught vision systems might begin to evolve. Microsoft Brings Back a Ghost from Your Desktop Past Clippy returns inside Copilot as a glowing orb named Mico Microsoft has given its AI assistant a new face, and it feels oddly familiar. The company has introduced Mico, a visual companion now built into Copilot on desktop and mobile. Mico shifts colors, changes shape, and reacts to voice, tone, and touch. Tap it enough times, and it reveals a full transformation into Clippy, the legendary paperclip that once lived in Microsoft Office. What’s new: • Interactive design. Mico now appears on the Copilot home screen and in voice mode. • Custom themes. Users can change its color or shape with a tap or voice request. • Hidden Easter egg. Repeated tapping turns Mico into Clippy for a brief nostalgic moment. • Wider rollout. The update is now reaching Android and iOS users in the United States. The reappearance of Clippy is more than nostalgia. It shows Microsoft’s interest in giving software a visible personality again. Mico is designed to watch, respond, and learn from human cues, turning Copilot into something that feels less like a tool and more like company. For Microsoft, the experiment is a study in emotion as much as technology. The company wants to see whether a friendly face can make AI more approachable, or whether reviving a ghost from the desktop past will only remind people how much the machines are learning to smile back. Claude Code Turns the Browser Into a Developer’s Test Lab Anthropic moves toward full-stack AI assistance Anthropic has begun testing Claude Code, a browser-based coding platform that hints at its bigger ambitions in software development. The preview is limited to Pro and Max users but shows how far the company wants to take its AI models beyond chat. ● Code in the cloud. Developers can launch tasks from the browser without local setup. ● GitHub connection. Claude can pull repositories, edit code, and submit pull requests on its own. ● Controlled execution. All activity runs inside a secure sandbox that isolates each task. ● Mobile preview. A new iOS version brings real-time tracking to phones. Claude Code looks less like a productivity tool and more like a test case for Anthropic’s next platform. The company is exploring how AI can take on engineering work directly inside cloud infrastructure. What starts as a coding helper could become Anthropic’s first step toward building an autonomous development environment. Mistral Just Built the DevOps Layer for AI The new AI Studio is Mistral’s bid to turn enterprise experiments into real, working intelligence Mistral AI has launched AI Studio, a serious step toward becoming the backbone of enterprise AI. The platform helps teams move from clever prototypes to dependable, production-level systems. It is available in private beta for a small group of corporate clients who need governance, visibility, and control over their AI workflows. What’s new: • Observability. Teams can trace, audit, and monitor model outputs in real time. • Agent Runtime. Built for complex AI pipelines that need reliable, continuous execution. • AI Registry. A central record of every model, version, and asset under enterprise governance. • Flexible deployment. Works across hybrid, on-premise, or Mistral-managed setups for full data control. The company built its reputation on model performance and open releases, but this move plants it squarely in the enterprise space where reliability and regulation rule the game. It is less about building a chatbot and more about building the pipes that keep corporate AI running. The timing matters. As Google, OpenAI, and Anthropic race to capture consumer attention, Mistral is quietly chasing the business layer that powers the real economy.\r\nFortsätt läsa på LinkedIn\r\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/apples-m5-chip-comeback-one-saw-coming-genai-works-mlt7f?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BKRdd92ZfQEqDM42cdEy4AQ%3D%3D&midToken=AQFnXqLnGXqsGA&midSig=1i6HJ7gQ3n_XY1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-newsletter_content_preview_text-0-readmore_button_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-newsletter_content_preview_text-0-readmore_button_-null-h01i2f~mh9qaam1~s1-null-null&eid=h01i2f-mh9qaam1-s1&otpToken=MTMwNTFjZTcxYjI3Y2NjNGIyMmQwZmViNDExOGU2YjI4ZmNiZDI0NDllYWU4OTZjN2JjZjA0NmQ0YTVkNTlmYWY1ZGNkNmU5NTZlNWU2ODIwZThiZDZiZGJkNGY1MThhYTI4Yzk3MmY3OGFmOTAzNmZhMTg2MWQ0LDEsMQ%3D%3D\r\n  \r\n      \r\n\r\n----------------------------------------\r\n\r\nDetta e-postmeddelande var avsett för Viktor Strindin (-)\r\nLäs mer om varför detta visas: https://www.linkedin.com/help/linkedin/answer/4788?lang=sv&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BKRdd92ZfQEqDM42cdEy4AQ%3D%3D&midToken=AQFnXqLnGXqsGA&midSig=1i6HJ7gQ3n_XY1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-SecurityHelp-0-textfooterglimmer&trkEmail=eml-email_series_foll